org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the Superior Court of the State of Washington
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Application of Jung Ham and Seid Yam for a Writ of Habeas Corpus,
This cause coming on to be heard on the petition of Jung Ham and Seid Yam, and the Court having duly considered the same and being fully advised in the premises, it is hereby

ORDERED that the said Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration appear in this court on the 28 day of October, 1920, at the hour of 10 o'clock G.M., and show cause why a Writ of Habeas Corpus should not be issued discharging and petitioners, Jung Ham and Seid Yam and each of them from custody. It is further

ORDERED that the said Henry M. White Commissioner of Immigration be and he is hereby commanded not tp permit or suffer the said Jung Ham and Seid Yam or either of them to be taken from the City of Seattle upon any pretext whatsoever until and unless this Court shall further order. It is further

ORDERED that this order shall be reserved by delivering a certified copy thereof, together with a copy of the petition to Henry M. White personally, or if he be absent, to the Deputy in charge of the Immigration Station at First and Union Streets, in the City of Seattle, Washington.
DONE in open court this 25th day of October, 1920.
